   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE FIRST STEP OF GOD'S SALVATION IN LIFE REGENERATION Scripture Reading: Gen 2:8-9; John 1:1, 4; Rom 5:10, 18b OUTLINE God's original desire and purpose: To be life to man Gen 2:8-9.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>With the tree of life as a symbol v. 9; Rev 2:7b; 22:2, 14, 19.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God's full salvation consisting of two great elements redemption and salvation: God's redemption, with the precious blood of Christ as the focus, meeting the need in the judicial aspect Rom 3:20-26; Eph 1:7.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>God's salvation, with the life of Christ the life of God as the focus, meeting the need for authority power Rom 5:10.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God's redemption dealing with man's fall; God's salvation carrying out God's intention, which is to give Himself as the Spirit to be life to man 2 Cor 3:6.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The redemption through Christ's precious blood laying the foundation and paving the way for the salvation in God's life Acts 11:18; Rom 5:17b-18, 21b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The four major steps of God's salvation in life regeneration, transformation, conformation, and glorification.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The definition of regeneration: To be begotten of God John 1:13.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To have God's eternal life in addition to man's natural life 3:16.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God's ordination: That man, who was chosen and created by God, should be regenerated in addition to being created Gen 2:9a.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>That man, who was fallen and dead in sins, should be redeemed and regenerated Acts 11:18.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The accomplishment of regeneration 1 Pet 1:3: Through Christ's resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>At the time of Christ's resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The experience of regeneration: Everyone who believes into Christ experiencing the regeneration which was accomplished through Christ's resurrection John 3:7.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>At the time they repent and believe into Christ v. 15.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The way to experience regeneration: To be born of water v. 5: To be convicted concerning sin 16:8-11.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To repent and confess our sins Acts 2:38.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To be born of the Spirit John 3:5: To call on and receive Christ Rom 10:13; John 1:12.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>To believe into Christ 3:36a.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The issue of regeneration: Becoming children of God with the divine life and the divine nature 1:12; 2 Pet 1:4; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Eph 4:18.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Being members of the household of God, those who are of the household of the faith 2:19; Gal 6:10.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Being indwelt by the Triune God the Father, the Son, and the Spirit Eph 4:6b; Rom 8:10a; John 14:17.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Becoming the brothers of Christ and being begotten of God the Father with Christ to become the many sons of God Rom 8:29b; Heb 2:10-12.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Being the members of Christ to be the increase of Christ 1 Cor 12:27; John 3:30a.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Constituting the Body of Christ as the fullness, the expression, of Christ Rom 12:5; Eph 1:23.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Becoming the new creation 2 Cor 5:17; Gal 6:15.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Becoming a part of the new man Eph 2:15; Col 3:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Entering into the kingdom of God and becoming citizens of God John 3:5; Eph 2:19.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Being citizens in the heavens Phil 3:20; Eph 2:6b.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Being Israel, God's elect Gal 6:16.</S>
   </TEXT>
